18775/LDS-Church-in-Japan-Moving-missionaries-making-donations.html |newspaper= [[Deseret News]] |first= Scott |last= Taylor |date= March 15, 2011 | location = Salt Lake City, Utah |accessdate= 2014-10-15 }}\n* {{citation |ref={{harvid|Church News, 2005}}|url= https://www.thechurchnews.com/archive/2005-10-22/this-week-in-church-history-27878 |title= This week in Church history |journal= [[Church News]] |date= October 22, 2005 }}\n* {{citation |ref=harv|last1=Toshiko|first1=Yanagida|title=Memoirs of the Relief Society in Japan, 1951\u20131991|journal=BYU Studies Quarterly|date=2005|volume=44|issue=2|pages=145\u2013154|url=https://scholarsarchive.byu.edu/byusq/vol44/iss2/6/}}\n* {{citation |ref={{harvid|LDS Church News, 1964}}|url= https://news.google.com/newspapers?nid=336&dat=19640418&id=Dc5SAAAAIBAJ&sjid=3X8DAAAAIBAJ&pg=6215,4145279 |title= Upsurge reported in new chapels in Orient |newspaper= [[LDS Church News]] |date= April 18, 1964 |page= 12|accessdate= 2014-10-15 }}\n* {{citation |ref=harv|last1=Walker|first1=Ronald W.|title=Strangers in a Strange Land: Heber J. Grant and the Opening of the Japanese Mission|date=1986|journal=Journal of Mormon History|volume=13|issue=1|url=https://digitalcommons.usu.edu/cgi/viewcontent.cgi?referer=https://www.google.com/&httpsredir=1&article=1013&context=mormonhistory|pages=20\u201343}}\n* {{cite book |last1=Wilkinson |first1=Greg |editor1-last=Goodman |editor1-first=Michael A. |editor2-last=Properzi |editor2-first=Mauro |title=The Worldwide Church: Mormoninsm as a Global Religion |date=2016 |publisher=Brigham Young University Religious Studies Center |location=Provo, Utah |isbn=9780842529730 |chapter=Is the LDS Church a Japanese New Religion?|ref=harv}}\n* {{Citation|ref=harv|last=Yukiko|first=Konno|date=1993|url=https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/ensign/1993/04/fujiya-nara-twice-a-pioneer?lang=eng|title=Fujiya Nara: \u2013 ensign|website=ChurchofJesusChrist.org|access-date=2018-03-15}}\n\n== Further reading ==\n* {{cite book |last= Britsch |first= Ralph Lanier |authorlink= R. Lanier Britsch |year= 1998 |title= From the East: The History of the Latter-Day Saints in Asia, 1851\u20131996 |place= Salt Lake City, Utah |publisher= Deseret Book |isbn= 1-57345-268-8 |lccn= 97036785 |oclc= 37606249 }} A Latter-day Saint affiliated publication of the history of the LDS church in Asia, includes more information about the history of the LDS church in other Asian countries such as Cambodia and Thailand.\n* {{cite news|last= Clark |first= Drew |date= 13 July 2014 |title= Samurai visiting Salt Lake in 1872 launched interactions between Japanese and Mormons |url= http://www.deseretnews.com/article/865606805/Samurai-visiting-Salt-Lake-in-1872-launched-interactions-between-Japanese-and-Mormons.html?pg=all |newspaper= [[Deseret News]] }} An article containing information about the Iwakura Mission to Utah in 1872.\n\n== External links ==\n* {{official website|https://jp.churchofjesuschrist.org/?lang=jpn}} {{in lang|ja}}\n:The official Japanese website of The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints.\n* [https://news-jp.churchofjesuschrist.org  Japan Newsroom] {{in lang|ja}}\n:Church news publication in Japan\n* [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bkh0gPf4Noc Interview with Japanese LDS Church member and computer programmer Matsumoto \"Matz\" Yukihiro]\n\n{{LDS-Asia|show}}\n\n[[Category:The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints in Japan| ]]\n[[Category:Christianity in Asia]]\n", "name_user": "DePiep", "label": "safe", "comment": "fix {{official website}}", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Church_of_Jesus_Christ_of_Latter-day_Saints_in_Japan"}
